# ⚙️ Technical SEO Rules

## robots.txt Best Practices

```
# Correct structure
User-agent: *
Disallow: /admin/
Disallow: /api/
Disallow: /private/
Disallow: /*?*           # Block URL parameters (careful!)
Allow: /api/public/      # Allow exceptions

# Always reference sitemap
Sitemap: https://yourdomain.com/sitemap.xml
Sitemap: https://yourdomain.com/sitemap-news.xml

# Googlebot specific rules
User-agent: Googlebot
Crawl-delay: 1           # Only if needed (avoid — slows Googlebot)
```

⚠️ **Never disallow**:
- CSS files (`/wp-content/themes/`)
- JavaScript files (`/static/js/`)
- Core pages unless intentionally private
- Image directories (unless thin content)

## Sitemap Standards

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<urlset xmlns="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9"
        xmlns:image="http://www.google.com/schemas/sitemap-image/1.1"
        xmlns:news="http://www.google.com/schemas/sitemap-news/0.9">
  <url>
    <loc>https://example.com/page/</loc>
    <lastmod>2025-01-15</lastmod>
    <changefreq>weekly</changefreq>   <!-- Optional hint, Google may ignore -->
    <priority>0.8</priority>           <!-- Optional hint, Google may ignore -->
    <image:image>
      <image:loc>https://example.com/image.jpg</image:loc>
      <image:title>Descriptive image title</image:title>
    </image:image>
  </url>
</urlset>
```

**Sitemap Rules**:
- Max 50,000 URLs or 50MB per sitemap file
- Use sitemap index for large sites
- Only include canonical, indexable URLs (200 status)
- Exclude noindex pages, paginated pages (unless using proper canonical)
- Update `<lastmod>` only when content actually changed

## Redirect Rules

### Apache (.htaccess)
```apache
# Force HTTPS
RewriteEngine On
RewriteCond %{HTTPS} off
RewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI} [L,R=301]

# Force www (choose ONE)
RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} !^www\. [NC]
RewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://www.%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI} [L,R=301]

# Force non-www (choose ONE)
RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^www\.(.+)$ [NC]
RewriteRule ^ https://%1%{REQUEST_URI} [L,R=301]

# Trailing slash consistency
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
RewriteRule ^(.*[^/])$ /$1/ [L,R=301]

# Custom page redirect
Redirect 301 /old-page/ https://example.com/new-page/
```

### Nginx
```nginx
# Force HTTPS
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com www.example.com;
    return 301 https://example.com$request_uri;
}

# Force non-www
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name www.example.com;
    return 301 https://example.com$request_uri;
}
```

### Next.js (next.config.js)
```javascript
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {
  async redirects() {
    return [
      {
        source: '/old-page',
        destination: '/new-page',
        permanent: true,  // 308 (use for SEO — preserves method)
      },
      {
        source: '/blog/:slug',
        destination: '/articles/:slug',
        permanent: true,
      },
    ]
  },
  async headers() {
    return [
      {
        source: '/(.*)',
        headers: [
          { key: 'X-Robots-Tag', value: 'index, follow' },
        ],
      },
    ]
  },
}
```

## Canonical Tag Rules

```html
<!-- Self-referencing canonical (always include) -->
<link rel="canonical" href="https://example.com/exact-page-url/">

<!-- For paginated series — point to self, NOT page 1 -->
<!-- Page 2 canonical = page 2 URL (not page 1) -->
<link rel="canonical" href="https://example.com/category/page/2/">

<!-- Cross-domain canonical (content syndication) -->
<link rel="canonical" href="https://original-source.com/article/">

<!-- AMP pages point to canonical HTML -->
<link rel="canonical" href="https://example.com/article/">
```

⚠️ **Canonical Pitfalls**:
- Never point canonical to a 404 or redirected page
- Never have canonical chains (A→B→C, just use A→C)
- Canonical must use the same protocol (https)
- Use absolute URLs, not relative

## Hreflang Implementation

```html
<!-- In <head> of every language version -->
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="https://example.com/en/page/">
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="pt-BR" href="https://example.com/pt/page/">
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="es" href="https://example.com/es/page/">
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="x-default" href="https://example.com/en/page/">
```

**Hreflang Rules**:
- Every page must reference itself
- Every page must reference all other language versions
- Use `x-default` for language selector or primary language
- Hreflang must be reciprocal (A points to B, B points to A)
- Use language-region codes: `en-US`, `pt-BR`, `es-MX`

## Core Web Vitals — Code Fixes

### LCP Optimization
```html
<!-- Preload LCP image -->
<link rel="preload" as="image" href="/hero-image.webp" 
      imagesrcset="/hero-320.webp 320w, /hero-640.webp 640w, /hero-1280.webp 1280w"
      imagesizes="100vw">

<!-- LCP image — never lazy load -->
<img src="/hero-image.webp" 
     alt="Descriptive alt text"
     width="1280" height="720"
     fetchpriority="high"
     loading="eager">
```

### CLS Prevention
```css
/* Always specify aspect ratio for images/videos */
img, video {
  aspect-ratio: 16/9;
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}

/* Reserve space for ads/embeds */
.ad-container {
  min-height: 250px;
  content-visibility: auto;
}

/* Avoid layout shifts from fonts */
@font-face {
  font-family: 'MyFont';
  src: url('/fonts/myfont.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-display: swap;    /* or 'optional' for critical fonts */
  size-adjust: 105%;     /* Match fallback font metrics */
}
```

### INP Optimization
```javascript
// Break up long tasks
function processLargeDataset(data) {
  return new Promise(resolve => {
    const chunks = chunkArray(data, 50);
    let index = 0;
    
    function processChunk() {
      const chunk = chunks[index++];
      // process chunk
      
      if (index < chunks.length) {
        // Yield to browser between chunks
        setTimeout(processChunk, 0);
      } else {
        resolve();
      }
    }
    processChunk();
  });
}

// Defer non-critical JavaScript
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  // Load analytics after user interaction
  document.addEventListener('click', loadAnalytics, { once: true });
  document.addEventListener('scroll', loadAnalytics, { once: true });
});
```

## Structured Data Validation

After implementing schema, always validate with:
1. **Google Rich Results Test**: https://search.google.com/test/rich-results
2. **Schema.org Validator**: https://validator.schema.org
3. **GSC Rich Results report**: Search Console > Enhancements

Common Schema errors to avoid:
- Missing required properties (check schema.org docs for each type)
- Invalid date formats (use ISO 8601: `2025-01-15T10:30:00+00:00`)
- Nested schemas not properly connected
- Image URLs returning 404
- Price without currency
- Review without `itemReviewed`
